{
  "name": "Sellf: Webhook Starter (Verify + Route)",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "sticky-overview",
      "name": "Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -760,
        -400
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 1,
        "width": 700,
        "height": 420,
        "content": "## Route all Sellf webhooks to your own automations (starter)\n\n### How it works\nThe one workflow to start from: [Sellf](https://github.com/jurczykpawel/sellf) - a self-hosted checkout platform for digital products - signs every webhook delivery with an `X-Sellf-Signature` HMAC header. This starter verifies the signature (Stripe-style, replay-protected, rotation-aware), acknowledges immediately, and routes each event type - `purchase.completed`, `lead.captured`, `waitlist.signup`, `access.expired`, `refund.issued`, plus an `other` lane for everything else - to its own placeholder branch. Replace the placeholders with your logic and you have a verified, future-proof Sellf integration hub.\n\n### Setup\n1. In Sellf admin open **Settings → Webhooks**, add an endpoint with this workflow's Production URL (the **Sellf Webhook** node) and copy the signing secret.\n2. Paste the secret into **Configuration (EDIT ME)**.\n3. See the red note on **Verify Signature** for one required n8n environment setting, then activate.\n4. Use Sellf's **Send test** button on the endpoint - the delivery lands on the `other` branch, proving the pipeline end to end.\n\n### Customization tips\nReplace each placeholder with real nodes, or delete lanes you don't need. Subscription events (`subscription.*`, `invoice.*`) arrive on `other` - add Switch rules when you start selling subscriptions."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-receive",
      "name": "Section: Receive & Verify",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -760,
        340
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 7,
        "width": 1120,
        "height": 380,
        "content": "## Receive & Verify\nAccepts the Sellf webhook and checks its HMAC signature before trusting the payload."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-route",
